üö´ 7. MISTAKES & WARNINGS (HOW TO LOSE THEM)
The "When I Was Your Age": Immediate disconnect. They don't care. Your world doesn't exist anymore.
The "It Gets Better": This feels dismissive. Validate the pain now.
The Shock Face: If they tell you something crazy, do not gasp. Stay neutral. If you freak out, they shut down.
The Snitch: Unless they are in danger, do not threaten to tell their parents immediately. You lose trust forever.

üîö 8. FINAL SUMMARY
They are not children. They are young souls navigating a digital war zone.
Treat them with the respect of a veteran, and they will share their war stories.
Listen. Validate. Guide.

